node.text: So happy to be an Ambassador for @vivolife 🌸 I have been using their products for yearssss now since they started up as a small business till today when they're doing SO INCREDIBLY WELL 👏🏼 I was so excited when they approched me to be an Ambassador because I truly use and love them! I use the protein shake the most (salted caramel YUM)  but they are a fully plant based company that provides errrrythung you need for workout performance and just keeping yourself feeling and looking cute 😂🙌🏾 as well as the products being extremely thought out and delicious I also appreciate their sustainability efforts AND that with every order a tree is planted 💛 USE CODE RADHI10 For 10% OFF YOUR ORDER 🌸💛stay tuned imma be sharing recipes and all sorts xxx

node.text: @womenofimpact ROUND 3!!! (link to full video in my bio) !!!! This is the third time my sweet friend @lisabilyeu and I have sat down to avaaa chat. And I am always just so shocked after because we get into such a beautiful flow we have healthy debate we discuss things and unpack them deeply. I love her so much and I really hope this conversation is useful in some way. It's almost like a therapy session for me, say things I didn't intend to felt things I didn't know I needed to.  It was CLEANSING 😂😂😅😅

node.text: Anyone got a cute cry face tutorial?🤦🏽‍♀️🤷🏻‍♀️ LISTENNN this was not how it was supposed to go..BUT THAS THE WAY IT WENT. Also called my mum after this and she said I KNEW IT you’ve been so snappy and short with me these past couple days I knew you were missing me..anyone else do that?  But also sending anyone away from their family so much love..We got this 💛💛

node.title: If you’re away from the people you love. I feel you 💛

node.text: DO U WANNA BE A BLESSING OR A LESSON ? All we can do is try ! 💛( I think the video was cut at the beginning but I’m saying *EVERY *PERSON...). 😂😂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Radhi Devlukia-Shetty on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Give it a little time, just push through that uncomfortable stage, the part where you want to go backwards, the part that feels like it's too hard to get past. promise you, if you do that you'll come out the other side and realise THIS is actually what feels right, this is what's was meant to be all along! You have the strength and ability to create a new normal, BELIEVE IT WITH ALL YOUR HEART AND MIND and then go do it! Radhi'.

node.text: YOU  GOT  THIS...You really do! getting through the discomfort pushing through that tough part to get where u need and want to be IS HARD AS HELL but nothing you can't handle will come your way. So do it FOR YOU. Cos you deserve goodness 💛

node.text: TODAY ISSSS THE DAY!!! guilt and shame are just clever avoidance techniques..don't do that to yourself, if u fell off track don't waste time feeling sad about it just get back up and take action and try again every day is a chance to reset 💛 HOW BLESSED we are to wake up everyday with that opportunity...USE IT..YOU GOT THIS 🥰

node.text: From me to you..incase you've never been serenaded before...NOW YA HAVE..BOLLYWOOD STYLE...the best kind.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Radhi Devlukia-Shetty on August 28, 2021. May be a black-and-white image of text that says 'Your family won't always be your friends and your friends can quickly become your family. It's not about what genes you have in common, it's about the qualities and values you share, the respect and love you exchange, the trust and care you honor. That common ground is what grows the seeds of true connection. Radhi'.

node.text: This one's a hard one to come to terms with FOR SURE. But sometimes people are brought into your life to just teach you the lessons you need to learn and those people can even be your family! You can build your own tribe..remember that ✨💛

node.text: Ooooh this ones a tough one BUT SO TRUE! You know why, because your pain is real to YOU and their pain is real to THEM. We disqualify others pain just because we feel ours is worse..instead of seeing one right and one wrong I’ve found working through each separately in your mind and just taking time to understand how and why the other person could feel that way has always helped me. DON’T GET ME WRONG my first reaction is usually Me feeling like I’m absolutely right (I’m not stubborn at all 😂😂😅🙄) but after I break it down and really think about them separately I see there really are two sides to most stories!
